The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring National Defense Transportation Day and National Transportation Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of an advanced transportation infrastructure to the economy and security of the United States. It acknowledges the dedicated professionals who build and maintain the transportation system, highlighting their role in supporting military readiness and emergency response capabilities. The article also mentions the Department of Transportation's efforts to improve infrastructure across America using funds from the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009. It recognizes the impact of transportation on economic growth and social mobility, referencing President Eisenhower's creation of the interstate highway system. The proclamation encourages sustainable development and quality public transportation to create livable and environmentally sustainable communities. It concludes by designating Friday, May 21, 2010, as National Defense Transportation Day and the week of May 16 through May 22, 2010, as National Transportation Week, urging all Americans to recognize the importance of the transportation system and the contributions of those who support it.